section.section:
In accordance with guidelines developed under paragraph (2) of this subsection, the center director or the director's designee may grant an inmate the privilege of leaving the confines of a center for the following purposes:
employment or seeking employment;
educational programs;
vocational training;
community and civic activities;
volunteer work;
athletic competition;
personal or family visits; or
other similar rehabilitative activities.

From the earnings of an inmate, the center director may deduct:
an amount determined by the director to be the cost of providing food, lodging, and clothing to the inmate;
actual and necessary food, travel, and other expenses incidental to the inmate's participation in work release and rehabilitation programs;
any amount required by court order or agreement of the inmate, and not otherwise deducted, for the support of dependents; and
court ordered restitution payments.
